{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:14:09.789Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Authentication Methods**\n\nI've zeroed in on the authentication process. It seems quite straightforward – they're using `localStorage.getItem(\"gff_ai_access_token\")` for JWT authorization. A missing token triggers a redirect to `/portal/login`. Subsequently, they're performing a GET fetch request to `/api/v1/projects` (or a similar endpoint).\n\n\n**Designing Backend Documents**\n\nI'm now focused on designing the `/api/v1/documents` endpoint and its counterpart, `/api/v1/documents/[id]`. I need to ensure a careful design. I'm also creating an internal design plan, focusing on page narrative (secure records display), visual metaphor (\"Cryptographic Enclave Vault\"), and the desired layout strategy for the new interface.\n\n\n**Mapping API Results**\n\nOkay, I'm now exploring how to map the results of `/api/v1/documents`. I've found `API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS` in `lib/api-auth.ts`, which should be helpful. This should help me better design my internal model.\n\n\n**Refining Data Structures**\n\nI'm now diving deep into the data structures, specifically the document schema. I've uncovered key properties like `id`, `title`, `fileSize`, `type`, `sha256`, and associated metadata. I've contrasted this with the `PortalDocument` interface to map the APIs' attributes to the expected portal values. I need to make some adjustments to the data structures.\n\n\n**Evaluating Document Mapping**\n\nI'm now determining how best to map backend document records to the existing portal interface. My current thought is to perform a client-side dynamic mapping of `ApiDocumentItem` to `PortalDocument`. I'm checking expected UI values, such as format, status (mapping `verified` to `approved`), and category to ensure compatibility and visual consistency.\n\n\n**Crafting Data Transformations**\n\nI'm now writing a mapper function within `app/portal/documents/page.tsx` to handle the conversion from `ApiDocumentItem` to `PortalDocument`. I'm focusing on ensuring accurate and robust mappings. For instance, I'm converting `\"PDF\"` `type` to `format` and `\"Sovereign Core Architectural Blueprint\"` to `name`. I'm incorporating rules for categories based on the documents' title and `type`. Also, I'm mapping `status` to \"Approved\" and keeping the visibility as is.\n\n\n**Implementing Category Logic**\n\nI've fleshed out the category determination logic within my mapper function. It now checks for keywords in the document title or type to assign categories like \"Proposals\", \"SOW\", \"Governance\", or \"Delivery Assets\". I've also added a more robust status mapping.\n\n\n**Resolving Project Mapping**\n\nI'm now refining the `ApiDocumentItem` to `PortalDocument` mapping. I'm focusing on the `project` property, specifically how it should be resolved. Currently, the `project` field is pulling the `client_name` from the API. I'm also examining the mock data to determine if a direct project ID mapping exists. I'm noting that `doc-801` is part of project `proj-001`, which corresponds to `\"Apex Sovereign Multi-Agent Lattice\"`. I need to resolve the project mapping.\n\n\n**Constructing API Routes**\n\nI'm now starting on `/api/v1/documents/route.ts` and `/api/v1/documents/[id]/route.ts`. I need to ensure the implementation is secure, so I'll be checking authorization and role-based filtering rules. To do so, I'm examining `/api/v1/projects/route.ts` as a reference. I'm focusing on user authentication.\n\n\n**Implementing Authorization Filters**\n\nI'm now implementing role-based access control (RBAC) filtering for document retrieval. I'm focusing on ensuring that non-\"gff\\_admin\" users only see documents associated with their client ID. I've designed the filtering logic and started to implement the function to process the JWT, retrieve the user information, and filter the documents accordingly. I'm also planning to support query parameter filtering, similar to the existing `/api/v1/projects` endpoint.\n\n\n**Filtering API Data**\n\nI'm now incorporating backend filters within my `/api/v1/documents/route.ts` implementation. I'm supporting `client_id`, `status`, `type`, and search query filters based on URL parameters. I've designed the code to retrieve parameters and apply filters to the API's internal array of documents.\n\n\n**Validating Caller Authority**\n\nI'm now integrating authentication and authorization within the API. I've focused on validating user roles and client IDs for data access, using a mock user database. I'm extracting user data from the JWT, applying checks to inactive users, and implementing logic to handle different authorization paths. I've also implemented error messages.\n\n\n**Refining Security Implementation**\n\nI'm now refining the security implementation within the API. I've focused on ensuring data integrity through comprehensive role and client ID verification within the document filters. I'm verifying the JWT and extracting the user's client association. I've enhanced the authorization checks for administrators. I'm also addressing forbidden access errors.\n\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T15:14:09.792Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"yxmbwfuz","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/documents/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiDocumentItem, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const typeFilter = searchParams.get(\"type\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let documents = Object.values(API_MOCK_DOCUMENTS) as ApiDocumentItem[];\n\n    // RBAC policy logic\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      documents = documents.filter(d => d.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Enforce client boundaries\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's documents.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filter\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        documents = documents.filter(d => d.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply specific filters\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      documents = documents.filter(d => d.status.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (typeFilter) {\n      const q = typeFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      documents = documents.filter(d => d.type.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      documents = documents.filter(d => \n        d.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        d.description.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        d.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        d.id.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, documents });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
